Instructions
- Define `TtsSegment` interface locally: `{ id: string; status: 'done' | 'missing' | 'error'; duration?: number; text?: string }`.
- Spawn: `child_process.spawn('python3', ['render_tts.py', ...(segments ?? []).flatMap(s => ['--segment', s])], { cwd: process.cwd() })`.
- Stream stdout/stderr: call `onLog(line)` for each line from both streams.
- For `GET /api/pipeline/tts-render/segments`: scan `outputs/tts/*.wav` with `fs.readdirSync`, cross-reference with segment IDs parsed from `tts_script.md`.
- Register executor: `registerExecutor('tts-render', ...)`.
- Export both `GET` and `POST` handlers. The `GET` handler for segments is in the same route file at `app/api/pipeline/tts-render/segments/route.ts` — note this is a separate file from the run route.
- Actually: the run endpoint is at `app/api/pipeline/tts-render/run/route.ts` and the segments list is at `app/api/pipeline/tts-render/segments/route.ts`. Include both in this file's deliverable section.

Deliverable
- `app/api/pipeline/tts-render/run/route.ts` — POST endpoint for TTS rendering with SSE streaming.
- `app/api/pipeline/tts-render/segments/route.ts` — GET endpoint listing TTS segments with status.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- `render_tts.py` is at project root and handles `--segment` filtering.
- Segment IDs are derived from `tts_script.md` heading markers.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
